OL,7,F"A ticking time bomb" is how Neil
OL,8,FWalker describes his life after being
OL,9,Fdiagnosed with hepatitis B, hepatitis
OL,10,FC, and HIV.
OL,12,FNeil's journey began when he was given
OL,13,Fcontaminated blood products as part of
OL,14,Fhis haemophilia treatment. .
OL,16,F"There had to have special measures
OL,17,Fput in place - full-time bodyguards,
OL,18,Fcarers, staff carrying bleach and
OL,19,Ffirst-aid kits, escorting me to
OL,20,Flessons, in case they had to clear it
OL,21,Fup. They had gloves and gowns."
